{"article_id":"jcz7QyhFI3V0YasE","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"\" The 360 \" shows you diverse perspectives on the day ' s top stories .","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Wednesday ' s vote","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"to impeach President Trump","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"marked the end of a painstaking ,","depth":10},{"id":4,"text":"and at times grinding , investigative process","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"that took place over the course of three months in the House of Representatives .","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"Impeachment now moves to a trial in the Senate ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"where there are indications","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"things may move at a much more accelerated pace .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"The ultimate outcome of the trial is almost certain .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"Even the most optimistic liberal forecasters find the likelihood","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that 20 Republicans","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"- the number","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"needed","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"to join Democrats in a vote","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"to convict and remove the president -","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"will break party ranks","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"to be close to unimaginable .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Trump is widely expected to survive the trial","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"and remain in office .","depth":6},{"id":20,"text":"The path to that expected conclusion is much less clear .","depth":6},{"id":21,"text":"The Constitution provides no formal outline","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"for how the Senate trial should be carried out .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"There are some existing rules from previous impeachments ,","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"but any of those could be changed by a simple majority vote .","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell has said","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"he wants an expedited trial ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"and on Tuesday he appeared to reject Democrats ' request for additional witnesses","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"who weren ' t interviewed in the House investigation .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Republican Sen. Lindsey Graham predicted","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"impeachment would \" die quickly \" in the Senate .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"With the outcome essentially determined ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"the substance of the trial takes on extra weight ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"as both parties hope to influence voters ' decisions in the 2020 election .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"There are currently 53 Republicans in the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"meaning McConnell can execute his plan for a speedy trial","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"as long as the caucus stays united .","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"Unless a handful of GOP senators break ranks ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"the Senate trial could be over in a flash with limited testimony and no new witnesses heard .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"\" We ought to vote","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"and move on , ''","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"McConnell said .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"The GOP has been remarkably cohesive during the Trump presidency ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"but a few senators might see political risk","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"in appearing to rush through impeachment","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"and may vote for rules","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"that could make the trial last longer .","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Supreme Court Chief Justice John Roberts ,","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"who will preside over the trial ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"could also try to produce a more substantial trial ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"although his powers are limited .","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"Another force","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"that could extend proceedings","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"is President Trump himself ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"who reportedly prefers a longer \" spectacle \" of a trial .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"After Wednesday ' s vote , House Speaker Nancy Pelosi said","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"she would hold off on sending the impeachment articles to the Senate","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"until she was confident","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"there would be a fair hearing .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"She didn ' t provide details","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"on what she would consider fair","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"or how long she might be willing to delay the exchange ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"but she could theoretically do so indefinitely .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"The Senate trial will be a rubber stamp in Trump ' s favor","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"\" With Republicans in control of the Senate , the president can rest easy","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"when it comes to the next stage of the impeachment proceedings. \"","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"- Julian Zelizar , CNN","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"The flimsy charges in the articles of impeachment should be dismissed quickly","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"\" All told , the House promised enough damning information against President Trump","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"to merit his indictment for the moral equivalent of carjacking .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Instead , the Democrats ' scrawny articles of impeachment do not equal a speeding ticket. \"","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"- Deroy Murdock , Fox News","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Republicans have no interest","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"in exploring the allegations against Trump","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"\" Rather than confronting the substance of the allegations against him ,","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"senators seem set on redirecting the focus of the trial to former Vice President Joe Biden ,","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"who Trump pressured Ukraine to investigate ,","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"and other figures like the whistleblower","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"whose complaint helped launch the impeachment inquiry .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"These counternarratives don ' t rebut the allegations","depth":13},{"id":80,"text":"Trump faces","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"so much","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"as they seek to distract from them. \"","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"- Li Zhou , Vox","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"The modern GOP doesn ' t care","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"whether Trump abused his office","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"\" The essential difference between Nixon and Trump lies not in their misconduct or in their unsuitability for office ,","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"but in the grim refusal of today ' s Republican Party to notice wrongdoing and its determination","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"to stand by Trump","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"come what may. \"","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"- Nicholas Kristof , New York Times","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"Chief Justice Roberts could use his influence","depth":4},{"id":92,"text":"to make the trial last longer","depth":4},{"id":93,"text":"\" Sen . Mitch McConnell supposes","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"that it ' s up to him to determine the way","depth":7},{"id":95,"text":"President Donald Trump ' s impeachment trial will proceed in the Senate .","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"... But McConnell is wrong :","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"It is Chief Justice John Roberts , not the majority leader , who will be making all the key decisions. \"","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"- Bruce Ackerman , Slate","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":197,"left":0,"right":196,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":196,"left":188,"right":195,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":188,"left":152,"right":187,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":117,"right":151,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":115,"right":116,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":115,"left":106,"right":114,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":103,"right":105,"relatio